<subSubSection pageId="63" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="63.[151,1436,1245,1980]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,341,1655,1681]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hardy" authorityYear="2006" box="[351,460,1656,1681]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Orafortis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[351,460,1656,1681]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Orafortis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a monotypic genus known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[963,1030,1656,1682]" name="Chile" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Chile</collectingCountry>
. For a detailed description of the adult female, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Kondo, T. &amp; Hardy, N. &amp; Cook, L. &amp; Gullan, P." box="[355,587,1693,1719]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="19 - 36" refId="ref50582" refString="Kondo, T., Hardy, N., Cook, L. &amp; Gullan, P. (2006) Description of two new genera and species of Eriococcidae (Hemiptera: Coccoidea) from southern South America. Zootaxa, 1349, 19 - 36." type="journal article" year="2006">
Kondo 
<emphasis box="[441,500,1693,1718]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">et al.</emphasis>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
, who considered that 
<taxonomicName box="[841,934,1693,1718]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Orafortis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luma">
<emphasis box="[841,934,1693,1718]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. luma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was superficially like 
<taxonomicName authority="Targioni Tozzetti" authorityName="Targioni Tozzetti" authorityYear="1868" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1199,1331,1693,1718]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Eriococcus</emphasis>
Targioni Tozzetti
</taxonomicName>
(all species currently in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Targioni Tozzetti" authorityYear="1868" box="[661,794,1731,1756]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[661,794,1731,1756]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Eriococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from South America are here considered to belong to other genera (See Appendix 1)) but can be distinguished from all those known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1199,1265,1768,1794]" name="Chile" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Chile</collectingCountry>
in having: (i) distinct sclerotic rims around dermal orifices of macrotubular ducts; (ii) sclerotic nodules on dorsal surface of posterior abdominal segments; (iii) microtubular ducts opening at bases of enlarged dorsal spinose setae; and (iv) 2 sizes of dorsal macrotubular ducts. Kondo 
<emphasis box="[751,813,1880,1905]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">et al.</emphasis>
discuss the differences between 
<taxonomicName box="[1215,1313,1880,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Orafortis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luma">
<emphasis box="[1215,1313,1880,1905]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. luma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other 
<taxonomicName authority="" box="[151,508,1917,1943]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Acanthococcus">
<emphasis box="[151,290,1917,1942]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Eriococcus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[310,497,1917,1942]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Acanthococcus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
species from 
<taxonomicName box="[686,816,1917,1943]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Myrtaceae</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[894,965,1917,1943]" name="Chile" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Chile</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kondo, T. &amp; Hardy, N. &amp; Cook, L. &amp; Gullan, P." box="[979,1227,1917,1943]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="19 - 36" refId="ref50582" refString="Kondo, T., Hardy, N., Cook, L. &amp; Gullan, P. (2006) Description of two new genera and species of Eriococcidae (Hemiptera: Coccoidea) from southern South America. Zootaxa, 1349, 19 - 36." type="journal article" year="2006">
Kondo 
<emphasis box="[1072,1127,1917,1942]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">et al</emphasis>
. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
also make some comments on the structure of the first-instar nymph of 
<taxonomicName box="[793,887,1955,1980]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Orafortis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luma">
<emphasis box="[793,887,1955,1980]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. luma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but do not describe it in detail.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
